Aeromarine Flying Cruiser
AIR CASTLES
MADE REAL
FOR this Key West Havana service six new
Aeromarine Flying Cruisers have been built,
each at a cost of over $50,000.
No possible item
of comfort, convenience or safety has been over-
looked.
No expense has been spared. You step
into a cabin as inviting as a drawing room.
Pas-
sengers have the same freedom of movement as
on a private yacht.
Comfortable and deeply upholstered wicker
chairs line the walls. For each chair there is a
special observation window. Attractive chintz.
hangings add to the feeling of ease as you watch
the splashing waves.
Have the truly inspira-
tional panoramic view which aviation alone pro-
vides.
From this beautifully
appointed cabin
watch vanishing Key West as it grows smaller
and smaller; get your first outlook down on Old
Moro with the sense of comfort and ease you
would have by the window of your own living
room at home.
